  "title": "construction supervisor",
  "description": "<p>A Construction Supervisor</p><p>oversees daily on-site operations, managing crews, subcontractors, and vendors to ensure projects are completed on time, within budget, and in compliance with safety regulations and building codes</p><p>. They inspect work quality, schedule tasks, and act as the key liaison between project managers and field staff.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Site Management:</strong> Direct daily operations, including material deliveries and equipment usage.</li><li><strong>Safety Compliance:</strong> Enforce strict adherence to safety regulations (e.g., OSHA) and conduct regular site inspections.</li><li><strong>Project Scheduling:</strong> Plan and coordinate construction phases to meet project deadlines.</li><li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Inspect work-in-progress to ensure it meets technical specifications and building codes.</li><li><strong>Coordination & Communication:</strong> Liaise between subcontractors, engineers, architects, and project managers.</li><li><strong>Resource Management:</strong> Supervise, train, and assign tasks to workers, as well as manage on-site material logistics. </li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills and Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Proven experience as a construction supervisor, foreman, or similar role.</li><li><strong>Knowledge:</strong> Deep understanding of construction procedures, materials, and project management principles.</li><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Ability to read and interpret construction blueprints, drawings, and plans.</li><li><strong>Leadership:</strong> Strong team management, decision-making, and communication skills.</li><li><strong>Education:</strong> High school diploma required; associate or bachelor’s degree in construction management is often preferred. </li></ul><p><strong>Typical Working Conditions</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Environment:</strong> Works on construction sites, often in various weather conditions.</li><li><strong>Requirements:</strong> Must wear personal protective equipment (PPE) and may travel to multiple sites. </li></ul>",
